smoothly between particles.</i>

22:41.458 --> 22:42.578
Okay, Elena...

22:42.917 --> 22:46.707
It was a pleasure.
You can call Pablo, you have his number,

22:46.875 --> 22:49.745
- if you want to hook up sometime.
- You don't want to come with me?

22:50.917 --> 22:52.207
Good morning.

22:54.125 --> 22:56.575
<i>Or what causes that tingle</i>

22:56.667 --> 22:58.707
<i>whenever we're about to see
the other particle.</i>

22:58.792 --> 23:01.082
- You can't come in here.
- I'm here to see Elena.

23:01.250 --> 23:02.330
You're Manel?

23:02.625 --> 23:04.955
Go ahead, you can stay on that side.

23:21.750 --> 23:23.540
<i>When the chemistry is intense,</i>

23:24.833 --> 23:26.883
<i>you really feel the electricity.</i>

23:27.000 --> 23:28.830
I'll be done in a little while.

23:39.292 --> 23:41.752
You're very organized, aren't you?

23:41.917 --> 23:43.707
No. You think?

23:44.958 --> 23:47.628
- Where's dinner?
- In the oven.

23:48.708 --> 23:50.378
And the dirty pans?

23:50.833 --> 23:52.333
Or clean ones?

23:52.500 --> 23:54.170
It's a question of method.

23:55.750 --> 23:58.210
How about some wine, Mr. Method?

23:59.417 --> 24:03.037
What's fascinating about science
is everything can be explained.

24:03.208 --> 24:05.538
For example, don't you think it's strange

24:05.750 --> 24:07.559
that with all the advances
we've made in biology,

24:07.583 --> 24:08.923
we still don't know what life is?

24:09.042 --> 24:11.292
That the famous mystery
still hasn't been revealed?

24:11.458 --> 24:12.708
I don't know, is it?

24:13.125 --> 24:14.955
Maybe there's nothing to reveal.

24:15.125 --> 24:16.415
That's what's amazing.

24:16.583 --> 24:20.423
Life is probably just a consequence
of how atoms organize themselves,

24:20.583 --> 24:23.383
another step in the evolution
of complex systems.

24:23.542 --> 24:25.132
That's why I study them.

24:25.958 --> 24:27.958
You're the one who's a complex system.

24:28.000 --> 24:30.670
We're just a bunch of organized atoms.

24:31.083 --> 24:34.543
Even if we think there's something
divine about life and we're in charge,

24:34.958 --> 24:38.208
everything is predetermined
by a few basic rules.

24:38.375 --> 24:39.875
How sad, right?

24:40.083 --> 24:42.963
I don't know, I'd rather think
there is a mystery

24:43.083 --> 24:44.383
and that life is special.

24:44.542 --> 24:45.882
If not, what's the point?

24:50.167 --> 24:53.917
This bunch of organized atoms has decided
it needs to go to the bathroom.

24:54.042 --> 24:55.162
Actually, you didn't decide.

24:55.250 --> 24:57.380
It was already decided
before you decided.

25:14.958 --> 25:16.168
You were saying?

25:17.125 --> 25:19.625
No. No, I forgot.

25:27.875 --> 25:30.245
I'll start emitting ultraviolet radiation.

25:52.042 --> 25:56.922
<i>Actually, weak force isn't so weak
nor difficult to detect.</i>

25:58.500 --> 26:01.330
<i>You just need to be in the right place.</i>

26:02.125 --> 26:04.915
<i>Within the atomic system, that force</i>

26:05.042 --> 26:06.752
<i>is felt with great intensity.</i>

26:11.458 --> 26:13.038
Tell me you don't snore.

26:14.083 --> 26:16.383
PHASE 1

26:25.250 --> 26:26.540
Hi!

26:28.000 --> 26:29.830
This is where you're preparing
your thesis?

26:31.958 --> 26:33.998
I got you a present,
I couldn't help myself.

26:34.708 --> 26:36.578
What? Why?

26:36.792 --> 26:38.332
Because it's not your style...

26:38.500 --> 26:41.460
And it proves that Mr. Method
is not a lost cause. There's still hope.

26:42.250 --> 26:43.710
It's beautiful.

26:45.667 --> 26:48.207
It's identical, how did you do it?

26:48.375 --> 26:51.375
I had to take the sculptor
to the park and make a cast.

26:51.542 --> 26:53.002
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

26:53.167 --> 26:55.167
We almost got caught. It was fun.

26:55.333 --> 26:58.253
I think it's the best present
anyone's ever given me.

27:04.750 --> 27:06.290
Get a room!

27:09.167 --> 27:11.077
Let's go to your place
and pick a spot for it.

27:48.292 --> 27:52.132
<i>Most people would say that
strong nuclear force is love</i>

27:52.708 --> 27:55.038
<i>because it makes particles
inseparable.</i>

27:55.458 --> 27:57.578
<i>But more careful analysis
demonstrates</i>

27:57.750 --> 27:59.830
<i>that it's actually more of a dependence.</i>

27:59.958 --> 28:00.998
Have a happy day.

28:01.417 --> 28:02.577
You too.

28:22.500 --> 28:24.880
<i>The farther away
the other particle gets,</i>

28:25.000 --> 28:26.750
<i>the more you need it.</i>

28:27.917 --> 28:30.167
<i>And when the rubber band breaks,</i>

28:31.000 --> 28:33.790
<i>things like the atomic bomb happen.</i>

29:17.083 --> 29:19.793
- Wanna hear a secret?
- Please.

29:20.708 --> 29:23.078
You're the first person I'm telling.

29:25.292 --> 29:26.832
I want to be an actress.

29:26.958 --> 29:29.328
Actually, it's what I've always
wanted to be...

29:29.750 --> 29:34.080
because I love the idea
of stopping being myself

29:34.250 --> 29:36.500
and pretending I'm someone else,
living other lives,

29:36.917 --> 29:39.827
meeting different people
with stories to tell...

29:39.917 --> 29:41.497
Do you remember the guy

29:41.583 --> 29:45.133
I was talking to after the photo shoot?
With the black hat?

29:45.917 --> 29:47.637
The one who was devouring you
with his eyes?

29:47.667 --> 29:48.957
Yeah, that one.

29:49.708 --> 29:53.958
He offered me the starring role
in a short film.

29:54.458 --> 29:58.208
I haven't read the script yet,
but I just decided I'm going to do it.

30:02.125 --> 30:04.325
Thanks for telling me your secret.

30:09.958 --> 30:12.498
<i>The question you're probably
asking yourselves</i>

30:12.708 --> 30:15.288
<i>is if two particles have
the same forces acting on them,</i>

30:15.458 --> 30:17.708
<i>do they feel them
with the same intensity?</i>

30:21.833 --> 30:23.833
I like y... being with you.

30:23.917 --> 30:25.287
Look what pretty bikes!

30:27.750 --> 30:28.500
<i>There you see.</i>

30:28.625 --> 30:30.625
<i>Some signs indicate that these forces</i>

30:30.708 --> 30:34.458
<i>might not have</i> exactly <i> the same</i>
<i>effect on both particles.</i>

30:36.125 --> 30:37.125
Tell me you don't snore.

30:37.292 --> 30:41.962
<i>For the other particle, the weak nuclear</i>
<i>force might be</i> too <i> weak.</i>

30:42.125 --> 30:45.375
I'm sorry, but I have trouble sleeping
in the same bed with someone else.

30:46.250 --> 30:49.000
<i>Or the electromagnetic charge
might not be</i>

30:49.083 --> 30:50.713
<i>complementary enough.</i>

30:53.042 --> 30:56.502
<i>Or the strong force rubber band</i>
<i>might be</i> too <i> elastic.</i>

30:56.708 --> 30:57.828
I missed you so much.

30:58.167 --> 31:00.417
For me the week flew by!

31:05.458 --> 31:10.328
<i>Not to mention that gravity
never stops acting on us.</i>

31:14.708 --> 31:16.378
You already hold hands in the street?

31:16.792 --> 31:18.752
Just the other day
and she found an excuse

31:18.833 --> 31:21.213
- right away to let go.
- But you see each other a lot.

31:21.292 --> 31:23.632
No, she's always too busy.

31:24.375 --> 31:25.875
Damn, this chick is hot.

31:26.250 --> 31:29.380
Sure you don't want to see?
She's a bombshell.

31:29.958 --> 31:32.958
They offered Elena this campaign,
but she couldn't do it.

31:33.125 --> 31:34.125
Better.

31:34.292 --> 31:38.752
You have no idea.
The other day after the photos,

31:38.833 --> 31:40.003
when we finished...

31:44.083 --> 31:46.503
Manel, you might be picking up
signals that aren't there.

31:47.125 --> 31:49.245
You're grabbing at straws.

31:49.708 --> 31:51.748
You guys have fun together, right?

31:51.958 --> 31:52.708
I do.

31:52.792 --> 31:54.502
Maybe she's just a little spooked.

31:54.708 --> 31:56.128
No, you notice stuff like that.

31:56.292 --> 31:58.559
Your body can tell if the other
person is falling in love or not.

31:58.583 --> 32:01.883
Damn, those are big words.
You're falling in love?

32:02.750 --> 32:04.750
I fell in love the day
we crashed into her.

32:06.292 --> 32:07.502
What about you?

32:07.708 --> 32:08.708
What about me?

32:08.833 --> 32:10.713
- With Eva.
- Fine.

32:10.875 --> 32:12.875
We hang out, have sex, good vibe.

32:13.417 --> 32:14.877
But are you...?

32:15.000 --> 32:16.130
What?

32:16.625 --> 32:17.825
No way.

32:18.625 --> 32:22.385
I wouldn't mind because she's fantastic, but no. - What about her?
- Her? No, she isn't either.

32:28.083 --> 32:29.753
Well, I don't think so.

32:30.042 --> 32:31.962
I hope not, she hasn't said anything.

32:32.375 --> 32:33.375
Damn.

32:34.000 --> 32:36.500
No, I don't think so. No.

32:36.625 --> 32:39.705
No, definitely not. Hell no.

32:39.875 --> 32:42.535
No, no, no.

32:43.958 --> 32:46.378
- At six?
- Yeah.

32:49.542 --> 32:51.172
Hi. What's up?

32:57.542 --> 32:58.832
Oops, sorry.

33:06.625 --> 33:10.375
Take my hand or I'll make a huge
fucking scene you won't believe.

33:11.542 --> 33:13.332
You're a son of a bitch.

33:14.125 --> 33:17.375
Why? I behave myself.
I treat her like a queen.

33:17.500 --> 33:20.880
- Like you do all the girls you fuck.
- Sure, I'm a gentleman.

33:21.750 --> 33:22.920
Thanks.

33:25.250 --> 33:26.960
Look, Manel.

33:27.792 --> 33:31.712
I think you need to relax
and give Elena time.

33:31.958 --> 33:34.628
Play it cool, make her miss you.

33:34.750 --> 33:38.750
Go out more, go to the gym,
meet women too...

33:39.417 --> 33:43.037
It won't matter,
the scale is already tipped.

33:43.125 --> 33:46.495
I think Elena and I have reached
our peak of happiness.

33:46.708 --> 33:49.078
Damn, with that attitude
no wonder she got spooked.

33:49.208 --> 33:52.038
It's not an attitude, it's science.
It's in the books.

33:52.208 --> 33:55.708
You don't know because all you think
about is getting laid, but the initial

33:55.792 --> 33:58.962
conditions within a system
are what determine its evolution.

33:59.083 --> 33:59.963
Huh?

34:00.083 --> 34:01.083
What?

34:01.250 --> 34:04.330
It's very simple. We have a system and
two parts with different temperatures.

34:05.958 --> 34:09.498
So the second law of thermodynamics
is already set in motion.

34:10.750 --> 34:12.210
What was the second law?

34:39.458 --> 34:41.038
Why aren't you answering?

34:56.208 --> 34:58.078
<i>But what is entropy?</i>

34:58.833 --> 35:01.253
<i>Get ready to understand
once and for all</i>

35:01.417 --> 35:03.977
<i>something you'll never forget.</i>
How hard is it to send a message?

36:10.292 --> 36:11.422
There's someone else.

36:31.333 --> 36:32.883
<i>But there's still more.</i>

36:33.417 --> 36:35.127
<i>There's another way
to look at entropy</i>

36:35.292 --> 36:38.712
<i>and it's even more troubling,
even more devastating.</i>

36:39.875 --> 36:42.125
I was up all night
gluing it back together.

36:42.292 --> 36:43.792
You didn't have to.

36:45.500 --> 36:47.250
It doesn't look so bad.

36:47.875 --> 36:50.455
- After all you went through to...
- It's okay.

36:50.625 --> 36:53.165
It has even more personality now.

36:55.708 --> 36:57.708
It wasn't such a pretty sculpture.

36:59.625 --> 37:02.495
I can't see you this week, Manel,
I'll be too busy with the short film.

37:05.667 --> 37:08.997
You can visit me on the set,
but I can't spend any time with you.

37:09.125 --> 37:11.035
You're leaving already?
You just got here.

37:11.167 --> 37:13.287
I'm sorry, I can't stay.
I have a rehearsal.

37:13.917 --> 37:15.917
- Is everything okay?
- I don't know.

37:16.083 --> 37:17.583
Is everything okay?

37:18.542 --> 37:20.712
You didn't answer my messages
yesterday.

37:20.875 --> 37:23.745
I didn't. Wow. I'm sorry I'm so busy.

37:23.833 --> 37:25.583
- Really.
- Is that all?

37:25.875 --> 37:27.535
That's all. Don't freak out.

37:28.125 --> 37:31.915
You might be going a little fast
for me. But everything's fine, okay?

37:32.500 --> 37:36.630
See you on Sunday. Come up with
some law of physics to explain to me.

37:37.458 --> 37:38.578
Wish me luck.

37:38.792 --> 37:39.962
Good luck.

38:17.833 --> 38:21.173
Hi, excuse me.
I'm here to see Elena, I'm Manel.

38:21.250 --> 38:23.920
Manel? Manel who?
They already left.

38:24.042 --> 38:26.082
But they told me they were here
ten minutes ago.

38:26.208 --> 38:29.918
They're shooting the rest of the day
somewhere else, like two hours away.

39:04.875 --> 39:06.495
Maybe we could do a threesome.

39:09.875 --> 39:12.035
PHASE 2

39:15.958 --> 39:17.288
I don't mean to...

39:17.875 --> 39:21.955
I <i> didn't</i> mean to startle you,
but I must say that your thesis

39:22.083 --> 39:24.213
is coming along more slowly
than expected.

39:24.375 --> 39:25.825
It sucks.

39:26.083 --> 39:28.383
It could also be expressed
that way, yes.

39:29.917 --> 39:31.827
Right now a lot of people
are working

39:31.958 --> 39:33.998
on thermodynamics
in complex systems.

39:34.167 --> 39:36.747
If you don't hurry up,
someone might beat you to it.

39:36.833 --> 39:39.293
I'm sick of thermodynamics
and complex systems.

39:41.125 --> 39:43.495
Did you know that
a large number of physicists

39:43.708 --> 39:46.668
who developed thermodynamics
committed suicide?

39:47.500 --> 39:50.380
Or even worse, they tried unsuccessfully.

39:51.042 --> 39:54.292
Some even lost their wives
and children while trying.

39:54.833 --> 39:56.963
The statistics are staggering.

39:57.083 --> 39:58.883
No, I didn't know.

39:59.792 --> 40:02.082
I'm telling you because you don't
look very enthusiastic.

40:03.250 --> 40:06.920
- I'm just tired. A bad night.
- Anyway,

40:07.042 --> 40:10.332
I only wanted to tell you that
your thesis is very promising,

40:10.500 --> 40:13.670
but you mustn't lose your edge.

40:15.250 --> 40:18.040
We're anxiously awaiting
your results.

40:18.833 --> 40:20.833
<i>I'll tell you about my night.</i>

40:21.208 --> 40:24.878
<i>Remember, we're talking about disorder
and lost energy here.</i>

40:27.708 --> 40:30.578
Have a seat! This is ready
and it gets cold fast!

40:31.458 --> 40:32.538
Hello?

40:34.333 --> 40:35.633
Shit, it's overdone.

40:36.625 --> 40:39.018
I'm sorry, I was in a hurry
and everything came out backwards.

40:39.042 --> 40:41.002
- If you'd told me a little sooner...
- Hi.

40:42.083 --> 40:43.633
Go on, sit down.

40:44.250 --> 40:47.380
It won't be great.
What are you drinking, wine?

40:47.542 --> 40:50.422
- I brought you a bottle.
- Open it and I'll start serving.

41:06.250 --> 41:08.250
I have a casting for a movie on Monday.

41:08.750 --> 41:12.880
I'm a little nervous,
so let's not get overwhelmed, okay?

41:13.000 --> 41:14.790
I'll help you clean up after.

41:14.958 --> 41:17.828
Yeah, okay. I just wanted
everything to be perfect

41:17.917 --> 41:20.167
- when you got here.
- I came to see you.

41:20.333 --> 41:22.713
And I'm sure your dinner is great.

41:30.250 --> 41:32.540
Wait, let me get this.

41:35.042 --> 41:39.172
My love, let's have dinner
and have a nice chat.

41:41.208 --> 41:42.828
- Okay?
- Okay.

41:47.458 --> 41:48.828
I'll make coffee.

41:50.750 --> 41:52.210
I'm not finished yet.

41:52.375 --> 41:54.325
That way it'll be ready
when you are.

41:57.208 --> 41:59.958
I'll clear the table while I'm at it.

42:19.083 --> 42:22.253
It's not the smoke, it's the smell
of food, it's too stuffy in here.

42:32.250 --> 42:34.080
I love this song.

42:34.917 --> 42:37.037
I'll turn it down a bit,
you hear everything up here.

42:37.208 --> 42:39.788
At least until we close the windows.
I'll do that in a second.

42:39.958 --> 42:41.958
Don't take the wine. Please.

42:42.333 --> 42:43.753
Yeah, right, sorry.

42:48.875 --> 42:50.375
You're fascinating, you know that?

42:51.708 --> 42:52.918
Look at your home.

42:53.042 --> 42:55.292
Your books arranged by subjects,

42:55.458 --> 42:57.628
your figures always perfectly placed,

42:57.833 --> 43:00.333
your pajamas neatly folded
by the bed...

43:01.500 --> 43:02.750
I admire you.

43:02.958 --> 43:04.418
I really do.

43:08.583 --> 43:11.963
But my love,
I think you need a little...

43:12.458 --> 43:13.878
What was this called again?

43:15.167 --> 43:16.167
Entropy?

43:18.583 --> 43:19.753
Sorry.

43:20.000 --> 43:21.130
I'm sorry!

43:24.958 --> 43:25.958
Wow.

43:26.500 --> 43:28.630
I wouldn't just call it entropy.

43:28.833 --> 43:31.173
I'd also call it... joy!

43:31.333 --> 43:33.583
Joy!

43:34.417 --> 43:35.827
What are you doing?

43:36.500 --> 43:38.000
- Will you stop?
- Joy!

43:38.167 --> 43:39.957
- Calm down for a second!
- Fly!

43:40.500 --> 43:41.790
Elena, please...

43:41.958 --> 43:43.958
Not the drawers... Okay, okay...

43:44.083 --> 43:45.803
- I was dying to do this.
- We have to talk.

43:47.958 --> 43:50.418
No, not the books, they're in order...

43:50.583 --> 43:52.753
- Come on, be happy with me.
- No, hold on.

43:52.917 --> 43:54.997
Wait, let's talk... Damn

43:55.625 --> 43:58.745
I'll stop cleaning up, I promise!

43:58.917 --> 44:01.837
That's enough, knock it off! <i>- We can't sleep, damn it!</i>
- Elena, please...

44:02.083 --> 44:04.463
<i>Some people have to work!</i>

44:04.625 --> 44:06.495
- Sorry!
- Come here...

44:06.708 --> 44:08.378
Let me free you, Mr. Scientific Method!

44:08.542 --> 44:09.752
Elena, let me go!

44:09.917 --> 44:11.627
You're repressed, don't you see?

44:14.750 --> 44:16.960
What's your problem?
You spoiled brat!

44:17.750 --> 44:20.830
You see? You never think
of the consequences!

44:20.917 --> 44:23.877
It's better than being 15 moves
ahead all the time!

44:24.000 --> 44:26.330
You've got Kasparov Syndrome!

44:26.500 --> 44:27.920
Yeah? And what's your thing called?

44:28.042 --> 44:30.172
When people only care
about themselves?

44:30.333 --> 44:32.003
Don't change the subject,
Mr. Method.

44:32.167 --> 44:34.327
You're turning into a pain in the ass!

44:34.500 --> 44:36.000
Oh, yeah. It's called "egocentritis."

44:36.167 --> 44:38.497
When your ego is bigger
than your head.

44:38.708 --> 44:40.828
What am I doing here
with a stick in the mud like you?

44:40.917 --> 44:42.517
You're here because
nobody can stand you.

44:42.625 --> 44:45.415
Your ego absorbs everything
like a black hole.

44:45.583 --> 44:46.963
And yours doesn't?

44:47.125 --> 44:50.245
All you want is for me to follow
you around like a puppy dog.

44:57.542 --> 45:00.082
Oh, great.
Now you're leaving, right?

45:00.250 --> 45:02.309
I think that's enough disorder
to keep you busy for a while.

45:02.333 --> 45:03.923
You see? That's what you're like.

45:04.042 --> 45:06.962
Things get messy and you
leave me here to clean it up.

45:07.083 --> 45:08.423
It's your mess.

45:11.042 --> 45:12.542
Give me the key, please.

45:12.792 --> 45:14.962
I gave you a copy, remember?

45:15.458 --> 45:18.248
I lost it, I forgot to tell you.
Will you please open the door?

45:18.375 --> 45:20.745
You lost the key to my flat?

45:20.958 --> 45:24.328
Great. Well, I don't know
where I put mine, I'm sorry.

45:24.500 --> 45:27.540
No,<i> I'm</i> sorry,
for being so clumsy...

45:27.875 --> 45:31.035
Please, go ahead and leave.
Everything is fine.

45:31.208 --> 45:33.038
Thanks for coming,
it was a pleasure.

45:33.208 --> 45:35.828
No, thank you, I had a blast.
You're a laugh a minute.

45:35.958 --> 45:37.998
You're too kind!

45:38.167 --> 45:41.377
No, really. I love being with you.
I'm going to miss you so much.

45:41.542 --> 45:42.382
Me too!

45:42.542 --> 45:44.422
I love you!

45:53.292 --> 45:56.332
Damn it!
I am such a fucking idiot!

46:01.208 --> 46:02.248
What was that?

46:03.917 --> 46:08.327
That was thermodynamics
reacting on my coffee pot.

46:18.833 --> 46:20.083
Thanks.

